  "excerpt": "Monte Carlo biscuits are a classic Australian biscuit: two lightly golden coconut-and-vanilla biscuits sandwiched together with butter cream and a smear of raspberry jam. They were introduced by Arnott's in the 1920s and have been a staple of Australian afternoon tea ever since. The homemade version is larger and more buttery than the packet original. The biscuit has a slight chew from the coconut and a crisp edge.",
