    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The dough is soft and easy to handle; rolled into balls and flattened with a fork, then baked until lightly golden. Do not take them past golden: the coconut continues to toast from the residual heat, and overbaked Monte Carloss are dry and hard. Leave them to firm up on the tray for 5 minutes before moving, as they are fragile while warm. Sandwich only once completely cool."
          }
        ]
      },
