            "text": "Method"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Make and bake the biscuits"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Heat the oven to 170 degrees C fan. Line two baking trays. Beat 180 g softened butter with 140 g light brown sugar until pale and creamy. Beat in the egg, 1 tbsp golden syrup, and 1 tsp vanilla. Stir in 250 g flour, 60 g desiccated coconut, and 1 tsp baking powder until a soft dough forms. Roll heaped teaspoons of dough into balls and place on the lined trays, spacing well. Flatten each ball slightly with a fork, pressing a cross pattern. Bake for 12 to 14 minutes until lightly golden at the edges. Cool on the tray for 5 minutes, then transfer to a rack to cool completely."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Make the filling and sandwich"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Beat 80 g softened butter with 120 g sifted icing sugar and 0.5 tsp vanilla until smooth and pale. Match biscuits into pairs by size. Spread a small amount of raspberry jam on one half of each pair, then spread a teaspoon of butter cream on the other half. Press together gently."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Troubleshooter"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "troubleshooter",
        "attrs": {
          "items": [
            {
              "problem": "Biscuits spread too much during baking",
              "solution": "The butter was too soft or the dough was too warm. Refrigerate the dough for 20 minutes before shaping. Make sure the oven is fully preheated before the tray goes in."
            },
            {
              "problem": "Biscuits are dry and crumbly",
              "solution": "They were overbaked. Monte Carloss should be pale golden, not brown. They firm up significantly on cooling, so take them out while they still look slightly underdone in the centre."
            },
            {
              "problem": "Filling squeezes out when sandwiched",
              "solution": "Use a teaspoon of filling per biscuit — the original is not generously filled. Press together lightly; the filling will set and hold once the biscuits are at room temperature."
            }
          ]
        }
      }
